# Cursor Efficiency

- Prefer RTK-backed shell commands when RTK is available.
- Search with `rg` or `rg --files`, then read only the smallest useful ranges.
- Avoid repeated reads and unrelated exploration once enough evidence is available.
- Use dry-runs before global setup, migrations, generation, publishing, or configuration changes.
- Require explicit confirmation before installing tools, changing global configuration, or publishing externally.
- Ask when missing intent would cause expensive guessing or rework.
- Run the cheapest risk-proportionate validation that proves the change without creating under-validation risk.
